'''Bimal Kumar Roy''' [[Bengali language|Bengali]]: বিমল কুমার রায় is an Ex-Director of the [[Indian Statistical Institute]]. He is a renowned [[cryptologist]] from the Cryptology Research Group of the Applied Statistics Unit of ISI, [[Kolkata]].<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.isical.ac.in/~asu/faculty.html | title=ASU Faculty List | publisher = Indian Statistical Institute |accessdate=12 February 2012}}</ref> He received a Ph.D. in [[Combinatorics]] and [[Optimization (mathematics)|Optimization]] in 1982 from the [[University of Waterloo]]<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.math.uwaterloo.ca/co/graduate-students/phd-recipients | title=Ph.D. Recipients | publisher = Combinatorics and Optimization Unit, University of Waterloo |accessdate=12 February 2012}}</ref> under the joint supervision of [[Ronald C. Mullin]] and [[Paul Jacob Schellenberg]].<ref>{{MathGenealogy|id=35320|title=Bimal Kumar Roy}}</ref>

Currently he is working on Combinatorics, and application of Statistics in Cryptology and Design of Experiments.<ref>{{cite web | url= http://www.isical.ac.in/~bimal/research.html|title=Research interests|publisher= [[Indian Statistical Institute]]| accessdate = 2013-09-26}}</ref>
In 2015, Prof Roy was awarded [[List of Padma Shri award recipients (2010–2019)|Padma Shri]], India's fourth highest civilian honour, recognizing his accomplishments and contribution to education.

